page.title: 09E. CHARMINSTER - FLOWERS 1
page.content: The chalky soil supports a profusion of wild flowers. The following were indentified at the beginning of July 1985: Agrimony Daisy Bedstraw yellow/white Dandelion Bird's foot trefoil Dog Daisy Bistort Forgetmenot Black bryony Foxglove Bluebell Geranium Bryony Germander speedwell Burdock Goosegrass Buttercup Guelder rose Campion red/white/bladder Hawkbit Cat's ear Hawkweed Chicory Hedge woundwort Clematis Honeysuckle Clover Hop trefoil Cow parsley Knapweed Cowslip Lamb's tongue Crane's bill
